&gt;I wholeheartedly agree.  Such a move also provides other countries
&gt;isolation from our twisted domain machinations.  For example, if the
&gt;new .net domain went away, or a new top-level domain were created, it
&gt;wouldn't inconvenience foreign mailers, who would be dealing with the
&gt;.us domain server.

Don't be too sure.  If the second level domain changed under this scheme
it would probably cause an equal number of problems.  Things are sort of
lopsided against the non-US sites as the root for everything is split
amoung three or four U.S. sites.

-Ron

